Under Justinian landowners (Dig. 2. 8. 15) and personae illustres (Cod. 12. 1. 17) could be compelled to bind themselves in iudicio permanere usque ad terminum litis only by a written cautio iuratoria ; it is not clear who were privileged to give a bare promise to this effect, though the edict seems to have con· tained careiul regulations on the subject, Gaius loc. cit: ‘pro tenore generalium edictorum’ Cod. r2. 22. 8.
